  "issue_number": 224,
  "issue_title": "Feature: add skill registry and enabled state",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\n\nLoaded skills are currently passed around as a simple list. Milestone 6 needs a registry that supports lookup, active skill selection, and enabled/disabled state.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd a `SkillRegistry` layer that can look up skills by ID, title, and alias. Persist enabled/disabled state locally, keep active-skill selection consistent with enabled skills, and expose deterministic lookup results for the agent and Settings UI.\n\n## User workflow\n\nA user can disable skills they do not want TouchPilot to use. The app should not match, select, or execute disabled skills.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nSkill availability and preferences remain local device state, preserving the local-first execution model.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\nDisabled skills must fail closed. If the active skill becomes disabled or unavailable, the app should clear or ignore that active selection rather than continuing under stale scope.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\nKeeping a raw list is enough for bundled demos, but it does not support user control or reliable matching.\n\n## Order note\n\nThis is PR 3 of 9. It depends on the v2 parser. Matching, enable/disable UI, and skill detail UI should build on this registry.",
